            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView18"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="1. Preheat the Oven:

Preheat your oven to 425°F (220°C).
2. Prepare the Potatoes:

Wash and scrub the potatoes. You can peel them if desired, but leaving the skin on adds extra crispiness.

Cut the potatoes into bite-sized cubes, ensuring they are roughly the same size for even cooking.

3. Season the Potatoes:

Place the potato cubes in a large bowl.

Drizzle olive oil over the potatoes, ensuring each piece is lightly coated.

Add garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, salt, and black pepper to the potatoes. Toss to evenly coat the potatoes with the seasoning.

4. Arrange on a Baking Sheet:

Spread the seasoned potato cubes in a single layer on a baking sheet. Use parchment paper for easy cleanup, if desired.

Make sure the potatoes have some space between them to ensure they crisp up rather than steam.

5. Roast in the Oven:

Place the baking sheet in the preheated oven.

Roast the potatoes for about 30-40 minutes, turning them with a spatula every 15 minutes or so, until they are golden brown and crispy.

6. Optional: Add Fresh Herbs:

About halfway through the cooking time, you can sprinkle fresh herbs, such as rosemary or thyme, over the potatoes for added flavor.
7. Serve:

Once the potatoes are crispy and golden, remove them from the oven.

Transfer the roasted crispy potatoes to a serving dish and serve immediately."
